  25:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****   ==============================================================================
  26:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****                         ##### How to use this driver #####
  27:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****   ==============================================================================
  28:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****     [..]
  29:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (#) Program the required configuration through the following parameters:
  30:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           the transfer mode, the output color mode and the output offset using
  31:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           HAL_DMA2D_Init() function.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\28576\AppData\Local\Temp\ccasxvWI.s 			page 2


  32:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
  33:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (#) Program the required configuration through the following parameters:
  34:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           the input color mode, the input color, the input alpha value, the alpha mode,
  35:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           the red/blue swap mode, the inverted alpha mode and the input offset using
  36:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           HAL_DMA2D_ConfigLayer() function for foreground or/and background layer.
  37:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
  38:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****      *** Polling mode IO operation ***
  39:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****      =================================
  40:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****     [..]
  41:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****        (#) Configure pdata parameter (explained hereafter), destination and data length
  42:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****            and enable the transfer using HAL_DMA2D_Start().
  43:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****        (#) Wait for end of transfer using HAL_DMA2D_PollForTransfer(), at this stage
  44:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****            user can specify the value of timeout according to his end application.
  45:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
  46:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****      *** Interrupt mode IO operation ***
  47:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****      ===================================
  48:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****      [..]
  49:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****        (#) Configure pdata parameter, destination and data length and enable
  50:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****            the transfer using HAL_DMA2D_Start_IT().
  51:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****        (#) Use HAL_DMA2D_IRQHandler() called under DMA2D_IRQHandler() interrupt subroutine.
  52:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****        (#) At the end of data transfer HAL_DMA2D_IRQHandler() function is executed and user can
  53:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****            add his own function by customization of function pointer XferCpltCallback (member
  54:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****            of DMA2D handle structure).
  55:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****        (#) In case of error, the HAL_DMA2D_IRQHandler() function calls the callback
  56:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****            XferErrorCallback.
  57:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
  58:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****          -@-   In Register-to-Memory transfer mode, pdata parameter is the register
  59:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****                color, in Memory-to-memory or Memory-to-Memory with pixel format
  60:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****                conversion pdata is the source address.
  61:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
  62:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****          -@-   Configure the foreground source address, the background source address,
  63:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****                the destination and data length then Enable the transfer using
  64:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****                HAL_DMA2D_BlendingStart() in polling mode and HAL_DMA2D_BlendingStart_IT()
  65:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****                in interrupt mode.
  66:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
  67:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****          -@-   HAL_DMA2D_BlendingStart() and HAL_DMA2D_BlendingStart_IT() functions
  68:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****                are used if the memory to memory with blending transfer mode is selected.
  69:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
  70:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (#) Optionally, configure and enable the CLUT using HAL_DMA2D_CLUTLoad() in polling
  71:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           mode or HAL_DMA2D_CLUTLoad_IT() in interrupt mode.
  72:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
  73:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (#) Optionally, configure the line watermark in using the API HAL_DMA2D_ProgramLineEvent().
  74:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
  75:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (#) Optionally, configure the dead time value in the AHB clock cycle inserted between two
  76:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           consecutive accesses on the AHB master port in using the API HAL_DMA2D_ConfigDeadTime()
  77:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           and enable/disable the functionality  with the APIs HAL_DMA2D_EnableDeadTime() or
  78:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           HAL_DMA2D_DisableDeadTime().
  79:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
  80:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (#) The transfer can be suspended, resumed and aborted using the following
  81:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           functions: HAL_DMA2D_Suspend(), HAL_DMA2D_Resume(), HAL_DMA2D_Abort().
  82:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
  83:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (#) The CLUT loading can be suspended, resumed and aborted using the following
  84:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           functions: HAL_DMA2D_CLUTLoading_Suspend(), HAL_DMA2D_CLUTLoading_Resume(),
  85:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           HAL_DMA2D_CLUTLoading_Abort().
  86:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
  87:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (#) To control the DMA2D state, use the following function: HAL_DMA2D_GetState().
  88:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
ARM GAS  C:\Users\28576\AppData\Local\Temp\ccasxvWI.s 			page 3


  89:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (#) To read the DMA2D error code, use the following function: HAL_DMA2D_GetError().
  90:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
  91:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****      *** DMA2D HAL driver macros list ***
  92:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****      =============================================
  93:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****      [..]
  94:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****        Below the list of most used macros in DMA2D HAL driver :
  95:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
  96:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (+) __HAL_DMA2D_ENABLE: Enable the DMA2D peripheral.
  97:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (+) __HAL_DMA2D_GET_FLAG: Get the DMA2D pending flags.
  98:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (+) __HAL_DMA2D_CLEAR_FLAG: Clear the DMA2D pending flags.
  99:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (+) __HAL_DMA2D_ENABLE_IT: Enable the specified DMA2D interrupts.
 100:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (+) __HAL_DMA2D_DISABLE_IT: Disable the specified DMA2D interrupts.
 101:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (+) __HAL_DMA2D_GET_IT_SOURCE: Check whether the specified DMA2D interrupt is enabled or not.
 102:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
 103:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****      *** Callback registration ***
 104:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****      ===================================
 105:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****      [..]
 106:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (#) The compilation define  USE_HAL_DMA2D_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
 107:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
 108:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           Use function @ref HAL_DMA2D_RegisterCallback() to register a user callback.
 109:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
 110:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (#) Function @ref HAL_DMA2D_RegisterCallback() allows to register following callbacks:
 111:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****             (+) XferCpltCallback : callback for transfer complete.
 112:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****             (+) XferErrorCallback : callback for transfer error.
 113:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****             (+) LineEventCallback : callback for line event.
 114:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****             (+) CLUTLoadingCpltCallback : callback for CLUT loading completion.
 115:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****             (+) MspInitCallback    : DMA2D MspInit.
 116:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****             (+) MspDeInitCallback  : DMA2D MspDeInit.
 117:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 118:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           and a pointer to the user callback function.
 119:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
 120:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (#) Use function @ref HAL_DMA2D_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
 121:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           weak (overridden) function.
 122:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           @ref HAL_DMA2D_UnRegisterCallback() takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 123:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           and the Callback ID.
 124:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           This function allows to reset following callbacks:
 125:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****             (+) XferCpltCallback : callback for transfer complete.
 126:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****             (+) XferErrorCallback : callback for transfer error.
 127:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****             (+) LineEventCallback : callback for line event.
 128:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****             (+) CLUTLoadingCpltCallback : callback for CLUT loading completion.
 129:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****             (+) MspInitCallback    : DMA2D MspInit.
 130:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****             (+) MspDeInitCallback  : DMA2D MspDeInit.
 131:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
 132:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (#) By default, after the @ref HAL_DMA2D_Init and if the state is HAL_DMA2D_STATE_RESET
 133:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           all callbacks are reset to the corresponding legacy weak (overridden) functions:
 134:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           examples @ref HAL_DMA2D_LineEventCallback(), @ref HAL_DMA2D_CLUTLoadingCpltCallback()
 135:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit callbacks that are respectively
 136:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           reset to the legacy weak (overridden) functions in the @ref HAL_DMA2D_Init
 137:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           and @ref HAL_DMA2D_DeInit only when these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand)
 138:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the @ref HAL_DMA2D_Init and @ref HAL_DMA2D_DeI
 139:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand).
 140:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
 141:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           Exception as well for Transfer Completion and Transfer Error callbacks that are not defin
 142:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           as weak (overridden) functions. They must be defined by the user to be resorted to.
 143:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
 144:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in READY state only.
 145:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           Exception done for MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks that can be registered/unregistered
ARM GAS  C:\Users\28576\AppData\Local\Temp\ccasxvWI.s 			page 4


 146:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           in READY or RESET state, thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used
 147:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           during the Init/DeInit.
 148:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 149:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           using @ref HAL_DMA2D_RegisterCallback before calling @ref HAL_DMA2D_DeInit
 150:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           or @ref HAL_DMA2D_Init function.
 151:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
 152:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           When The compilation define USE_HAL_DMA2D_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 153:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           not defined, the callback registering feature is not available
 154:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****           and weak (overridden) callbacks are used.
 155:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c **** 
 156:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****      [..]
 157:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_dma2d.c ****       (@) You can refer to the DMA2D HAL driver header file for more useful macros
